{{Infobox rail line | box_width = | name = Lizza di Piastreta | color = | logo = | logo_width = | image = Parte della lizza di Piastreta.jpg | image_width = 270px | caption = View of the track | type = [[Monorail]] | system = | status = | locale = {{flagicon|Italy}} [[Massa]] ([[Italy]]) | start = Piastreta | end = Renara | stations = none (5 zones crossed) | routes = | daily_ridership = | open = 1922 | close = 1975 | reopen = | owner = | operator = | character = | depot = | stock = | linelength = {{convert|3.5|km|mi|abbr=on}} | tracklength = | tracks = | gauge = | minradius = | electrification = | maxincline = | racksystem = | speed = <!--{{convert|x|km/h|abbr=on}}--> | elevation = | map = | map_state = }} [[File:Edificio di servizio alla lizza di Piastreta.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Service building in the area of Fosso del Chiasso]]
The '''Lizza di Piastreta''', also known as '''Monorotaia di Piastreta''' ("Piastreta Monorail"), was an [[Italy|Italian]] [[Industrial railway|industrial]] [[monorail]] serving the [[Quarry|marble quarry]] of '''Piastreta''', in the [[Apuan Alps]], and linking it to '''Renara''', in the municipal territory of [[Massa]], [[Tuscany]].<ref name=a>{{it icon}} [http://www.alpiapuane.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=202:la-lizza-di-piastreta&catid=16:escursioni&Itemid=28 Article on alpiapuane.com]</ref>
==History== The monorail was projected in 1922 by the [[England|English]] engineer [[Charles Denham (engineer)|Charles Denham]], owner of the quarry of Piastreta.<ref name=a/> The line, used to carry the [[marble]] from the quarry to the valley, consisted of a single rail on wooden sleepers, on which a motorized tractor hauled a sled load. The system of the sleds was already used, for the transport of marble, also in other ''[[Via di lizza|vie di lizza]]'' (i.e. "routes of contention"),<ref>{{it icon}} [http://www.appennino.tv/lappennino-e-la-storia/item/418-vie-di-lizza-sulle-alpi-apuane Vie di Lizza on the Apuan Alps] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140221235606/http://www.appennino.tv/lappennino-e-la-storia/item/418-vie-di-lizza-sulle-alpi-apuane |date=2014-02-21 }}</ref> on other trials used for the ''[[lizzatura]]''.<ref>{{it icon}} [http://www.lanazione.it/massa_carrara/cronaca/2013/08/07/931371-lizzatura.shtml Article about the ''Lizzatura''] (''[[La Nazione]]'')</ref> This was the only plant of its kind to be built, and the track was realized in the workshops of [[Sesto San Giovanni]], near [[Milan]].<ref name=b>{{it icon}} [http://www.archeominerario.it/documenti/elenco_siti_beni_parco.PDF List of possible heritage sites in the Apuan Alps National Park (see page 5)]</ref>
In 1959 the course was shortened to Pianel Soprano, closing the route to Renara. Reopene in 1962, the line was active until 1975, when a road for [[truck]]s was opened.
The line is still intact, except for some portions disappeared due to erosion. The line, also named ''Lizza della Monorotaia'' or ''Monorotaia Denham'',<ref name=c>{{it icon}} [http://www.paesiapuani.it/monte%20sella%20da%20renara%20via%20monorotaia.htm Article on paesiapuani.it]</ref> is part of a route of [[industrial archaeology]] and, since 2003, like many lizzas in the basin of Massa, it is included in the Archaeological Park of the Apuan Alps.<ref name=b/>
==Route== The monorail starts in the quarries of Piastreta (1,580&nbsp;m), below the [[Sella (mount)|Sella]] mountain, and reaches Renara (310&nbsp;m),<ref>{{it icon}} [http://www.profiliapuani.altervista.org/itinerari/2renara_sella.htm Article on "profili apuani" website]</ref> a zone near the village of [[Gronda (Massa)|Gronda]], 9&nbsp;km far from [[Massa]]. From an altitude of 995 m begins its descent through a channel called "Fosso del Chiasso", where the slope reaches 90% until the end of the trail at the hill of load. In this section the rail is flanked by a staircase of 2,500 steps that allowed the miners to reach the caves.<ref name=a/><ref name=c/>
{| class="wikitable sortable" !width="150px| Zone !width="260px| Notes |- |'''Piastreta''' |Location: {{coord|44.08818|10.23938}} |- |'''Fosso della Piastrella''' |Quarrymen's shelter |- |'''Fosso del Chiasso''' |Service building |- |'''Pianel Soprano''' |Also named "Canale della Buchetta" |- |'''Renara''' |Location: {{coord|44.07508|10.21693}} |}
